    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Removal - High-pressure Oil Rail</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.2.2" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>High-pressure Oil Rail</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, it is recommended that the case-to-head tubes be replaced each time they
                    are removed. The D-rings are not replaceable. If you reuse the case-to-head tubes, you assume the
                    risk for leakage. You must inspect each D-ring carefully for evidence of cutting, abrasion or
                    twisting and never reuse a tube exhibiting any of these seal conditions.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e300511" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08027.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Removing the case-to-head plug from high-pressure rail (left side)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the case-to-head plug assembly with a &#189; inch breaker bar.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300512" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj08/j08028.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Removing the case-to-head plug</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift out case-to-head plug assembly and discard.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>On occasion, the case-to-head tube (lower) will come out along with the case-to-head plug. If this
                    occurs, discard entire case-to-head tube assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_81.xml" xrefid="e300517">case-to-head tube assembly</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e300513" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08029.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Location of oil rail bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the seven hex head bolts (M6 x 40) securing the oil rail assembly to the
                rocker arm carrier.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300514" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08030.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the oil rail assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift oil rail assembly straight away from injectors and case-to-head tube assembly. Allow
                oil to drain back to the sump or other suitable container.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not remove the 1&#188; x 20 UNF oil rail end plugs or single ball
                    tubes. Service parts are not available to support these components.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e300515" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj08/j08065.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Non-serviceable oil rail components</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Single ball tube (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil rail end plug (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
